{
  "texts": [
    "To contribute to this, we provided the examples above based on our own efforts and those of others.",
    "Now that we have described methods that can be used to develop comprehensive construct definitions, we will describe how to work with DCTs in research and in practice.",
    "DCT specifications can be used in research on two levels: that of the lab, institution, or learned society and that of the individual researcher or student.",
    "Organizations can maintain dedicated Decentralized Construct Taxonomies, which can then be used by the affiliated researchers and students.",
    "This minimizes hidden heterogeneity within the lab, institution, or learned society, ensuring that the results can be synthesized relatively effortlessly and with minimal risk of bias as a consequence of differences in construct definitions, measurement, or qualitative elicitation or coding."
  ]
}